

### HTML (index.html)
This HTML structure defines the main components of the welcome page, including a navigation bar with placeholder links for other sections of the website, and a welcome message section.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Welcome to Mountain Madness 2024</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Log In</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Sign Up</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Upload Photos</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Change Profile</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Change Background</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="welcome-section">
            <h1>Welcome to Mountain Madness 2024</h1>
            <p>Join us for an adventure of a lifetime.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>Â© 2024 Mountain Madness</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (style.css)
This CSS file includes basic styling for the welcome page, including styles for the navigation bar, the welcome section, and a background image. Adjustments can be made based on the specific designs seen in the "Welcome Page.png".

```css
body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-image: url('wallpaper1 1.png');
    background-size: cover;
}

header nav ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #333;
    overflow: hidden;
}

header nav ul li {
    float: left;
}

header nav ul li a {
    display: block;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    text-decoration: none;
}

header nav ul li a:hover {
    background-color: #111;
}

.welcome-section {
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
    padding: 20px;
}

footer {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
}
```

These code snippets provide a starting point. You might want to replace `'wallpaper1 1.png'` in the CSS with the correct path relative to where your CSS file is located or use it as a direct link if you're hosting the image online.

